into English for me?

17:57.008 --> 17:59.135
Uh, yeah.

18:15.626 --> 18:19.187
- Hello?
- Uh, Mr. Wigand, please?

18:19.263 --> 18:23.301
Someone's calling
for Daddy, Mom.

18:26.404 --> 18:28.736
- Oh. Thank you, Bob.
- Who's calling?

18:28.806 --> 18:31.001
Uh, my name
is Lowell Bergman.

18:31.075 --> 18:35.774
- Did you say "Berman"?
- No, Bergman. B-E-R-G-M-A-N.

18:35.846 --> 18:38.371
- I'm a producer for <i>60 Minutes.</i>
<i>- 60 Minutes?</i>

18:38.449 --> 18:41.418
- Yeah.
<i>- 60 Minutes,</i> the television show?

18:41.485 --> 18:44.886
- Yes.
- He doesn't want to talk to you.

18:47.124 --> 18:49.888
How does he know he doesn't
want to talk to me? He doesn't
know what I'm calling him about.

18:49.960 --> 18:52.520
He doesn't care to know.

19:14.618 --> 19:17.781
<i>This is the Wigands'.</i>

19:17.855 --> 19:21.347
<i>If you'd like to leave a message</i>
<i>or send a fax, start now.</i>

19:21.425 --> 19:24.394
<i>This is Lowell Bergman with</i> 60 Minutes,
<i>and I'm doing a story...</i>

19:24.462 --> 19:26.521
<i>on fire safety</i>
<i>and cigarettes.</i>

19:26.597 --> 19:29.691
<i>I have scientific documents</i>
<i>from a tobacco company,</i>

19:29.767 --> 19:32.531
<i>and I could use your help</i>
<i>as a consultant...</i>

19:32.603 --> 19:34.537
<i>explaining these documents</i>
<i>to me.</i>

19:34.605 --> 19:40.510
<i>Now, my number is</i>
<i>area code 510-555-0199.</i>

19:40.578 --> 19:45.345
<i>I'll be there at this number</i>
<i>in ten minutes.</i>

22:13.831 --> 22:16.891
If you're curious
to meet me,

22:16.967 --> 22:21.927
I'm gonna be in the lobby
of the Seelbach Hotel in Louisville...

22:22.006 --> 22:26.033
<i>reading</i> The New York Times
<i>tomorrow at 5:00.</i>

23:44.687 --> 23:47.281
<i>Have you always lived in Louisville?</i>

23:47.356 --> 23:51.486
Mr. Bergman, what did you
want me to consult about?

23:51.561 --> 23:55.088
Who's that?

23:56.766 --> 24:00.031
That's room service.

24:00.102 --> 24:02.866
They usually
knock first.

24:02.939 --> 24:05.134
Come on in.

24:05.208 --> 24:07.301
Over here, please.

24:16.285 --> 24:20.619
- Thank you.
- How do you like your coffee? Black?

24:20.690 --> 24:23.682
Black. Black.

24:23.759 --> 24:26.785
I really don't have that much time.

24:29.031 --> 24:31.693
Is there anything you want to know
about me, Mr. Wigand?

24:31.767 --> 24:33.894
Like what?
Your sign?

24:37.240 --> 24:39.299
I know what I
have to know.

24:39.375 --> 24:43.175
Just so I know you know,
when I talk to people in confidence,

24:43.246 --> 24:45.180
it stays that way.

24:47.617 --> 24:51.519
How did a radical journalist
from <i>Ramparts</i> magazine end up at CBS?

24:54.357 --> 24:56.848
I still do
the tough stories.

24:56.926 --> 24:59.292
<i>60 Minutes</i> reaches
a lot of people.

25:01.464 --> 25:03.659
Let me see
the documents.

25:31.894 --> 25:34.021
This is a, um,

25:34.096 --> 25:37.998
fire-safety product study
for Phillip Morris.

25:38.067 --> 25:42.026
Burn rates, ignition propensity,
things of this nature.

25:42.104 --> 25:44.971
I could very easily explain this
to you in layman's terms...

25:45.041 --> 25:46.975
because it's from
another company.

25:47.043 --> 25:50.809
- But that's as far as I go.
- As far as you go where?

25:51.881 --> 25:53.815
This issue is
a drop in the bucket.

25:53.883 --> 25:55.908
I can talk to you
about what's in here, but I...

25:55.985 --> 25:58.613
I can't talk to you
about anything else.

26:02.725 --> 26:05.922
I signed a confidentiality agreement.
I honor agreements.

26:09.999 --> 26:12.399
Doesn't CBS have confidentiality
agreements, Mr. Bergman?

26:12.468 --> 26:16.336
Between journalists and management,
yes, I believe they do.

26:16.405 --> 26:19.738
But I don't take that seriously.
Where do you work?

26:19.809 --> 26:21.743
Did work.

26:21.811 --> 26:25.941
<i>- Did</i> work?
- How much would I get paid?

26:29.285 --> 26:32.777
That you have to discuss
with CBS Business Affairs.

26:32.855 --> 26:37.485
But for something like this, I would
say anywhere between ten, 12 thousand.

26:41.430 --> 26:43.523
Should I just take
the documents now?

26:44.767 --> 26:47.292
If you want to do it.

26:53.943 --> 26:56.605
I worked as a, uh,

26:56.679 --> 26:59.580
head of Research and Development
for Brown & Williamson.

26:59.649 --> 27:02.140
Tobacco company.

27:05.388 --> 27:08.118
I was a corporate
vice president.

27:09.592 --> 27:11.958
Mr. Bergman.

27:39.388 --> 27:41.356
<i>President Assad of Syria said...</i>

27:41.424 --> 27:44.587
<i>that difficult obstacles remain,</i>
<i>but that his country,</i>

27:44.660 --> 27:49.097
"looks forward to a great long peace
with Israel."

27:49.165 --> 27:51.656
That's a Peabody, Mike.

27:51.734 --> 27:54.828
When you're dead and buried, this is
the one they're gonna remember you by.

27:57.039 --> 27:59.303
- Are you eating with us?
- Yeah.

27:59.375 --> 28:03.106
- Bring a tie so they let us
in the front door.

28:03.179 --> 28:05.272
Come on.

28:12.521 --> 28:15.183
- Debbie!
<i>- Hey, Lowell.</i>

28:15.257 --> 28:18.055
Oh, Bill. Main Justice is investigating
a major New York bank...

28:18.127 --> 28:20.595
laundering narco dollars
out of their Mexico City branch.

28:20.663 --> 28:22.722
- You want it for the news?
- What about you? You got a crew already?

28:22.798 --> 28:25.790
- I'm gonna do a follow-up.
Catch you later.
- Okay.

28:30.873 --> 28:32.807
- Debbie.
- How are you?

28:32.875 --> 28:36.311
I want you to get Legal on a corporate
confidentiality agreement.

28:36.378 --> 28:38.778
- Okay.
- Boundaries of their constraint,

28:38.848 --> 28:41.783
Kentucky state law about...

28:41.851 --> 28:43.785
<i>- I want you to drop everything.</i>
- Okay.

28:43.853 --> 28:46.185
- I don't have any change.
You got some change?
<i>- Oh, here.</i>

28:55.097 --> 28:57.088
Tony.

29:12.381 --> 29:15.111
<i>Mr. Wigand? You can go up now.</i>

29:37.839 --> 29:40.103
Sorry. I'm accepting
an award...

29:40.174 --> 29:43.940
from the Retinitis
Pigmentosa Foundation.

29:44.012 --> 29:46.378
It's gonna kill
the rest of my day.

29:52.020 --> 29:56.150
So, have you had a chance
to play golf?

29:56.224 --> 30:00.058
Jeff's a premier golfer.
What are you, a two handicap?

30:00.128 --> 30:03.359
- Seven.
- And he gets out there...

30:03.431 --> 30:06.093
and he has
five strokes on us.

30:06.167 --> 30:09.432
He has more concentration
than anybody I've ever met.

30:09.504 --> 30:12.962
It's spooky
how he can concentrate.

30:15.910 --> 30:18.174
I'd rather play
than talk about it.

30:19.781 --> 30:22.477
What did you
want to see me about?

30:22.550 --> 30:24.484
I don't like
being back here.

30:24.552 --> 30:27.316
Jeffrey says exactly
what's on his mind.

30:27.388 --> 30:30.323
Most people consider
what they're saying... social skills.

30:30.391 --> 30:33.326
Jeffrey just charges
right ahead.

30:33.394 --> 30:38.388
Now, I know you understood the nature
of the confidentiality portion...

30:38.466 --> 30:41.333
of your severance agreement
with Brown & Williamson.

30:41.402 --> 30:44.337
- Chapter and verse.
- Yeah, I know you do.

30:44.405 --> 30:48.364
You know, I came up
through sales.

30:48.443 --> 30:50.809
One of the reasons
I was a great salesman...

30:50.878 --> 30:53.938
was I never made a promise
I couldn't keep.

30:54.015 --> 30:56.745
I knew that if I ever
broke my promise,

30:56.818 --> 30:59.514
I'd suffer
the consequence.

30:59.587 --> 31:01.452
