Nobody will be able
to say, "Well, hell's bells, Margaret,

32:16.130 --> 32:18.690
I didn't know <i>that</i>
was a secret."

32:18.766 --> 32:22.031
We're very serious
about protecting our interests.

32:22.103 --> 32:24.867
We'd like you
to sign it.

32:26.407 --> 32:28.568
And if I don't?

32:28.643 --> 32:32.101
If we arrive at the conclusion
that you're acting in bad faith,

32:32.180 --> 32:36.116
we would terminate right now
payoffs under your severance package,

32:36.184 --> 32:41.315
you and your family's medical
benefits and initiate litigation
against you, Mr. Wigand.

32:42.790 --> 32:46.726
<i>- Dr.</i> Wigand.
<i>- Dr. Wigand.</i>

32:46.794 --> 32:50.457
<i>If you've examined the document, you'll</i>
<i>see it's in your own best interest...</i>

32:50.531 --> 32:52.658
and you'll sign it.

32:58.439 --> 33:02.933
What you're saying is it isn't enough
that you fired me for no good reason.

33:03.010 --> 33:05.035
Now you question
my integrity?

33:05.112 --> 33:09.776
On top of the humiliation
of being fired, you threaten me,

33:09.851 --> 33:13.184
you threaten
my family.

33:13.254 --> 33:16.382
It never crossed my mind
not to honor my agreement.

33:16.457 --> 33:19.426
I will tell you, Mr. Sandefur...
and Brown & Williamson too...

33:19.494 --> 33:22.691
Fuck me?
Well, fuck you!

33:32.540 --> 33:35.703
I'm not sure
he got the message.

33:35.776 --> 33:38.506
Oh, I think he did.

33:50.958 --> 33:52.721
- Yeah.
- You fucked me!

33:53.961 --> 33:56.521
- Who's this?
- Protect your sources?

33:56.597 --> 33:58.531
You screwed me.
You sold me out.

34:00.401 --> 34:05.073
- What are you talking about?
Where are you?
- Fuck you too!

37:27.875 --> 37:30.173
Stay away from me.

37:31.545 --> 37:33.945
You stay away from me!

37:42.123 --> 37:45.058
Jeffrey, you forgot
the lunches!

37:51.265 --> 37:53.529
<i>- Mrs. Wigand?</i>
- Jump in quick. Come on.

37:53.601 --> 37:57.162
How do you do? I'm Lowell Bergman.
We spoke on the phone.

37:59.273 --> 38:02.299
- Come here. I want to talk to you.
- Good. I want to talk to you.

38:02.376 --> 38:05.277
- This is my house.
In front of my wife, my kids?
- I did not burn you.

38:05.346 --> 38:07.541
I did not give you up
to anyone.

38:07.615 --> 38:10.778
- What business do we have?
- I'm here to straighten
something out with you.

38:10.851 --> 38:12.819
Right here, right now.

38:12.887 --> 38:15.515
You haven't mentioned my name?
You haven't talked to anybody about me?

38:15.589 --> 38:17.022
- What am I gonna mention your name for?
- Why are Brown & Williamson...

38:17.091 --> 38:19.025
How the hell do I know about
Brown & Williamson?

38:19.093 --> 38:22.551
It happened just after I talked to you.
I do not like coincidences.

38:22.630 --> 38:25.565
Well, I don't like paranoid accusations.
I'm a journalist.

38:25.633 --> 38:29.763
Think. Use your head.
How do I operate as a journalist?
By screwing the people...

38:29.837 --> 38:34.069
who could provide me with information
before they provided me with it?

38:34.141 --> 38:37.508
- You came all the way
down here to tell me that?
- No, I did not.

38:37.578 --> 38:39.637
Big Tobacco
is a big story,

38:39.714 --> 38:42.080
and you got something
important to say. I can tell.

38:42.149 --> 38:45.710
But yes, I did. I came all
the way down here to tell you...

38:45.786 --> 38:48.846
Story, no story...
fuck your story.

38:50.424 --> 38:53.222
I don't burn people.

39:24.158 --> 39:26.888
Ride with me while I
take the girls to school.

39:55.856 --> 39:58.086
<i>My little girl has acute asthma.</i>

39:58.159 --> 40:01.856
Deborah, my oldest daughter.

40:01.929 --> 40:05.296
And I'm unemployed, so I have
to protect my medical coverage.

40:07.468 --> 40:11.427
So I left them a message
this morning. Their expanded
confidentiality agreement...

40:13.574 --> 40:16.270
I will sign it.

40:16.343 --> 40:19.107
- They're afraid of you, aren't they?
- They should be.

40:25.886 --> 40:28.719
Talk to me outside the zone
of your agreement.

40:28.789 --> 40:32.850
- Like what?
- Like, uh, where'd you work
before Brown & Williamson?

40:32.927 --> 40:35.225
Johnson &Johnson.

40:35.296 --> 40:37.321
Union Carbide in Japan.

40:37.398 --> 40:40.856
I was the general manager and director
of new products. I speak Japanese.

40:40.935 --> 40:45.269
I was a director
of corporate development at Pfizer.

40:45.339 --> 40:47.967
All health-related.

40:50.444 --> 40:52.435
What else
outside the zone?

40:54.782 --> 40:57.376
I don't know. Do you think the Knicks
are gonna make it to the semifinals?

41:10.630 --> 41:12.461
- Just give me an example.
- Okay.

41:12.532 --> 41:15.399
For example, um,
James Burke.

41:15.468 --> 41:17.561
- C.E.O. Of Johnson &Johnson.
- Yeah.

41:17.637 --> 41:22.472
When he found out that some lunatic
had put poison in Tylenol bottles,

41:22.542 --> 41:24.476
he didn't argue
with the F.D.A.

41:24.544 --> 41:27.206
He didn't even wait for the F.D.A.
To tell him. He just pulled Tylenol...

41:27.280 --> 41:31.649
off every shelf of every store
right across America, instantly.

41:31.718 --> 41:34.881
And then he developed a safety cap.

41:34.954 --> 41:39.550
Because as a C.E.O., sure, he's
gotta be a great businessman, right?

41:39.626 --> 41:42.060
But he's also
a man of science.

41:42.128 --> 41:47.430
He's not gonna allow his company
to put on the shelf a product
that might hurt people.

41:47.500 --> 41:49.593
Not like
the Seven Dwarfs.

41:49.669 --> 41:52.433
- Seven Dwarfs?
- Seven C.E.O. S of Big Tobacco.

41:52.505 --> 41:54.598
They got in front of Congress
that time. It was on television.

41:54.674 --> 41:57.370
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Swore under oath that
they know nothing about addiction...

41:57.443 --> 41:59.434
It was on C-SPAN.
Yeah.

41:59.512 --> 42:04.609
Okay, so, here you are.
You-You-You go to work for tobacco.

42:04.684 --> 42:07.585
You come from corporate cultures
where research...

42:07.654 --> 42:10.316
really creative thinking...
these are core values.

42:10.390 --> 42:13.757
You go to tobacco.
Tobacco is a sales culture...

42:13.826 --> 42:16.886
market and sell enormous volume,
go to a lot of golf tournaments.

42:16.963 --> 42:19.227
The hell with everything else.
What are you doing?

42:19.299 --> 42:22.029
- Why are you working
for tobacco in the first place?
- I can't talk about it.

42:22.101 --> 42:24.831
The work I was supposed to do...

42:24.904 --> 42:27.964
might have had some positive effect,
I don't know.

42:28.041 --> 42:32.740
Could have been beneficial.
Mostly, I got paid a lot.

42:32.812 --> 42:36.077
I took the money.
My wife was happy.

42:36.149 --> 42:39.414
My kids had good medical,
good schools. Got a great house.

42:39.485 --> 42:41.715
I mean, what the hell
is wrong with that?

42:41.788 --> 42:44.348
Nothing's wrong with that. That's it.
You're making money.

42:44.424 --> 42:47.086
You're providing for your family.
What could be wrong with that?

42:50.163 --> 42:53.929
I always thought of myself as a man of
science, that's what's wrong with it.

42:55.935 --> 42:59.029
Then you're in
a state of conflict, Jeff.

42:59.105 --> 43:01.801
Because look,
here's how it lays out.

43:01.874 --> 43:03.842
If you've got vital
insider stuff,

43:03.910 --> 43:06.572
the American people, for their
welfare, really do need to know,

43:06.646 --> 43:08.614
and you feel impelled
to disclose it...

43:08.681 --> 43:11.878
and violate your agreement
in doing so, that's one thing.

43:11.951 --> 43:15.853
On the other hand, if you want
to honor this agreement,

43:15.922 --> 43:18.186
then that's simple...
you do so.

43:18.257 --> 43:20.452
You say nothing,
you do nothing.

43:20.526 --> 43:23.757
There's only one guy
who can figure that out for you,

43:23.830 --> 43:26.663
and that's you
all by yourself.

43:32.805 --> 43:34.932
I gotta go pick up the girls.
They only had a half a day.

43:54.360 --> 43:57.056
<i> I've heard virtually</i>
<i>all the... We touched on it...</i>

43:57.130 --> 44:00.861
<i>- Yes or no, do you believe</i>
<i>nicotine is not addictive?</i>
<i>- Congressman,</i>

44:00.933 --> 44:06.132
<i>cigarettes and nicotine clearly</i>
<i>do not meet the classic</i>
<i>definitions of addiction.</i>

44:06.205 --> 44:08.867
- There is no intoxication.
- We'll take that as no.

44:08.941 --> 44:10.932
Again, time is short.

44:11.010 --> 44:13.570
I think each of you believe
nicotine is not addictive...

44:13.646 --> 44:16.012
<i>and just would like to</i>
<i>have this for the record.</i>

44:16.082 --> 44:20.143
I believe that nicotine
is not addictive.

44:20.219 --> 44:22.619
I too believe
that nicotine...

44:22.689 --> 44:25.715
<i>He referred to this...</i>
<i>the Seven Dwarfs...</i>

44:25.792 --> 44:28.784
- What Seven Dwarfs?
<i>- The seven C.E.O. Of Big Tobacco...</i>
<i>referred to this.</i>

44:28.861 --> 44:32.888
Said they should be afraid of him.
I assume afraid of what he could reveal.

44:32.965 --> 44:37.834
Now you tell me. What does this guy
have to say that threatens these people?

44:37.904 --> 44:40.065
Well, it isn't cigarettes
are bad for you.

44:40.139 --> 44:42.403
- Hardly new news.
- No shit.

44:44.043 --> 44:48.571
- What's this?
<i>- What that is is tobacco's</i>
<i>standard defense.</i>

44:48.648 --> 44:50.582
It's the "we don't know"
litany.

44:50.650 --> 44:54.484
Addiction? We believe not.
Disease? We don't know.

44:54.554 --> 44:57.387
We take a bunch of leaves,
we roll them together, you smoke 'em.

44:57.457 --> 45:00.790
After that, you're on your own.
We don't know.

45:00.860 --> 45:02.919
<i>So, that</i>
<i>tells me nothing.</i>

45:02.995 --> 45:06.226
- Besides, you'll never get
what he's got.
- Why not?

45:06.299 --> 45:08.358
<i>Because of this guy's</i>
<i>confidentiality agreement,</i>

45:08.434 --> 45:10.800
he's never gonna be able
to talk to you.

45:10.870 --> 45:13.498
That's not good enough.
This guy is the top scientist...

45:13.573 --> 45:16.041
in the number-three
tobacco company in America.

45:16.109 --> 45:20.068
He's a corporate officer.
You never get whistle-blowers
from Fortune 500 companies.

45:20.146 --> 45:22.842
This guy is
the ultimate insider.

45:22.915 --> 45:25.941
He's got something to say. He wants
to say it. I want it on <i>60 Minutes.</i>

45:26.018 --> 45:28.145
Doesn't matter what he wants.
<i>Am I missing something here?</i>

45:28.221 --> 45:31.486
- What do you mean, Mike?
- He's got a corporate secrecy agreement.

45:31.557 --> 45:33.787
Give me a break.

45:33.860 --> 45:37.694
This is a public health issue, like an
unsafe air frame on a passenger jet...

45:37.764 --> 45:40.562
or some company dumping cyanide
into the East River.

45:40.633 --> 45:43.329
Issues like that.
He can talk, we can air it.

45:43.402 --> 45:46.929
They've got no right to hide behind
a corporate agreement. Pass the milk.

45:47.006 --> 45:49.668
They don't need the right.
They got the money.

45:49.742 --> 45:53.109
The unlimited checkbook.
That's how Big Tobacco wins...

45:53.179 --> 45:55.170
every time
on everything.

45:55.248 --> 46:00.413
They spend you to death.
$600 million a year in outside legal.

46:00.486 --> 46:04.422
Chadbourne-Park, Ken Starr's firm,
Kirkland and Ellis.

46:04.490 --> 46:07.186
Listen, G.M. And Ford,
they get nailed...

46:07.260 --> 46:10.252
after 11 or 12 pickups
blow up, right?

46:10.329 --> 46:13.526
- These clowns have never... I mean ever...
<i>- Not even once.</i>

46:13.599 --> 46:17.091
Not even with hundreds of thousands
dying each year from an illness...

46:17.170 --> 46:20.833
<i>related to their product have ever</i>
<i>lost a personal injury lawsuit.</i>

46:20.907 --> 46:24.308
On this case, they'll issue gag orders,
sue for breach... anticipatory breach...

46:24.377 --> 46:29.144
enjoin him, you, us,
his pet dog, the dog's veterinarian,

46:29.215 --> 46:32.651
tie 'em up in litigation for ten
or 15 years, I'm telling you,
they bat a thousand.

46:32.718 --> 46:36.449
Every time. He knows that.
That's why he's not gonna talk to you.

46:43.529 --> 46:47.397
<i>Okay, let's look through</i>
<i>the looking glass the other way.</i>

46:47.466 --> 46:50.060
What do you mean?

46:50.136 --> 46:52.502
We got a guy who wants to talk,
but he's constrained.

46:52.572 --> 46:55.735
- What if he were compelled to talk?
- Oh, torture. Great ratings.

46:55.808 --> 46:57.969
What do you mean, "compelled"?

46:58.044 --> 47:01.207
I mean, compelled
by a, uh, Justice Department.

47:01.280 --> 47:03.441
State courts.
Be a witness.

47:03.516 --> 47:06.747
That would cut through any
confidentiality agreement, wouldn't it?

47:06.819 --> 47:09.185
- What does that do?
- What do you mean, what does it do?

47:09.255 --> 47:12.588
What I mean is like, how does it cut
through the confidentiality agreement?

47:12.658 --> 47:15.491
Because he has to, uh,
reveal it in a court of law.

47:15.561 --> 47:18.325
It's on record. It's out.
It's no secret anymore.

47:18.397 --> 47:22.231
So how can they restrain his speech
or retaliate? It's out in the world.

47:22.301 --> 47:24.929
If you could engineer it into the
court record, you might have something.

47:25.004 --> 47:28.030
They would have a hell of a time
trying to restrain his speech
then, wouldn't they?

47:28.107 --> 47:31.873
Yeah, but what venue? And where does
he get... Does he have killer attorneys?

47:31.944 --> 47:34.845
I don't think he's got
any attorneys.

47:34.914 --> 47:38.475
<i>He's gonna need attorneys who aren't</i>
<i>afraid of risking years of litigation...</i>

47:38.551 --> 47:42.885
and millions of dollars
of their own dough in legal costs.

47:42.955 --> 47:45.446
What do you say, Mike?
What do you think?

47:48.060 --> 47:50.551
Even if he gets
the defense team,

47:55.067 --> 47:57.627
will he go for it?

48:03.743 --> 48:06.871
You're awfully
overqualified, Dr. Wigand.

48:13.619 --> 48:16.053
I'm trying to start
a new career.

48:17.957 --> 48:20.016
I believe I could be
a good teacher.

48:24.864 --> 48:26.798
Let me give it
some thought.

48:31.337 --> 48:35.569
And not a lot of companies in the health
care field hire ex-tobacco scientists.

49:09.841 --> 49:11.775
That's it.

49:20.085 --> 49:23.020
It's where
our babies were born.

49:26.791 --> 49:29.157
Debbie took her first steps
right there on...

49:31.263 --> 49:33.197
In the grass.

49:36.268 --> 49:39.863
- I didn't plan on this.
- Hey, hey, hey.

49:39.938 --> 49:42.031
Come on. Come on.

49:46.077 --> 49:50.241
We can make this
work for us. Okay?

49:50.315 --> 49:52.249
It's just...
It's not...

49:52.317 --> 49:55.150
It's just...
It's a smaller scale.

49:55.220 --> 49:59.122
Simpler, easier.

49:59.190 --> 50:03.422
More time.
More time together.

50:03.495 --> 50:05.759
More time
with the kids.

50:05.830 --> 50:08.663
More time for us.
Okay? It's just...

50:11.503 --> 50:15.166
Can you imagine me
coming home from some job...

50:15.240 --> 50:17.401
feeling good
at the end of the day?

50:19.878 --> 50:21.812
This is gonna be better.

50:24.516 --> 50:26.814
This is gonna be better.

50:45.503 --> 50:48.267
<i> Love your home</i>
<i>with beautiful Broyhill furniture...</i>

50:50.508 --> 50:54.638
<i>You'll find incredible</i>
<i>sale prices throughout Smith's</i>
<i>Broyhill showcase gallery,</i>

50:54.713 --> 50:57.944
<i>with extra savings on every style</i>
<i>for every room in your home.</i>

51:05.557 --> 51:09.084
<i>If you've been putting off</i>
<i>decorating that special room,</i>

51:09.160 --> 51:13.119
<i>now's the time to act during the</i>
<i>love-your-home sale at Smith's.</i>

51:14.499 --> 51:16.831
<i>- Back to...</i>
<i>- Welcome back.</i>

51:32.250 --> 51:34.684
Hey, baby.
What's wrong?

51:34.753 --> 51:36.880
Who's that outside,
Daddy?

51:39.090 --> 51:41.854
- Did you see somebody
or did you hear them?
- I heard him.

51:43.495 --> 51:46.089
- Where?
- In the backyard.

52:03.014 --> 52:05.881
Sit at Daddy's desk, okay?
Why don't you sit up at the desk.

52:05.950 --> 52:07.884
All right?

52:07.952 --> 52:12.048
Get out some paper,
and draw me a picture. Okay?

52:17.595 --> 52:21.725
What are you gonna draw me, baby?
An animal? Something like that?

52:21.800 --> 52:24.963
You stay down here until Daddy
gets back, all right, Barbara?

52:25.036 --> 52:26.970
You stay down here.

53:24.329 --> 53:26.661
You almost got
your damn head blown off.

54:06.504 --> 54:08.438
Daddy!

54:09.541 --> 54:13.341
It was just a raccoon, baby.
Nothin'.

54:13.411 --> 54:15.902
They're nocturnal.
You know what that means?

54:15.980 --> 54:18.414
That means that they
only come out at nighttime.

54:31.496 --> 54:33.513
- Yeah.
- Lowell. Jeffrey Wigand.

54:33.548 --> 54:35.530
- Yeah.
- Lowell. Jeffrey Wigand.

54:35.599 --> 54:38.898
<i>Is it too late?</i>

54:38.969 --> 54:41.062
No, no, it's okay. I...

54:41.138 --> 54:43.072
How-How's the new place?

54:43.140 --> 54:45.540
The new place?
New.

54:45.609 --> 54:49.045
- You okay?
- Sure.

54:49.113 --> 54:52.549
I was thinking of
calling you tomorrow anyway.

54:52.616 --> 54:57.280
- Uh, how's your kids,
uh, handling the new house?
- Good.

54:57.354 --> 55:00.585
- You got kids?
- We have a couple.

55:00.658 --> 55:04.617
One's hers, one's mine.
Everybody uses a different name.

55:04.695 --> 55:06.629
Modern marriage.

55:06.697 --> 55:08.892
Uh, how's Liane?

55:10.634 --> 55:13.933
Uh, she's okay. Uh...

55:14.004 --> 55:15.938
Hold on a minute.

55:22.680 --> 55:25.114
Lowell.

55:25.182 --> 55:28.379
Somebody may be following me. I-I don't
know. They came on the property.

55:28.452 --> 55:31.717
What do you mean, following you?
Did you call the police?

55:31.789 --> 55:34.781
I-I don't wanna be paranoid.
I mean...

55:34.859 --> 55:38.556
- Maybe it's a game.
Some kind of mind game.
- What do you really think?

55:38.629 --> 55:40.563
I don't know what the fuck
I really think.

55:40.631 --> 55:43.623
Are they doing it?
Is some crank doing it?

55:43.701 --> 55:45.635
Are they doing it
to make me feel paranoid?

55:45.703 --> 55:48.604
Are they doing it for real and don't
give a shit what I think? I don't know.

55:48.672 --> 55:51.573
- I don't fuckin' know.
- Jeffrey, describe for me...

55:51.642 --> 55:53.610
in detail what happened.

55:53.677 --> 55:55.702
Well...

55:55.780 --> 55:59.341
No. Look, I mean, there was
a footprint. Forget it.

55:59.416 --> 56:01.907
It's probably
not important at all.

56:01.986 --> 56:06.855
You know, I got a job now. I'm teaching
high school. Japanese and Chemistry.

56:08.893 --> 56:12.090
Uh, so, uh, what were you
calling about?

56:12.163 --> 56:15.621
- You called me.
- No, you said you were gonna
call me tomorrow.

56:15.699 --> 56:18.497
- So, what about?
- Oh, yes, yes, yes. I did.
I wanted to talk to you.

56:18.569 --> 56:23.302
I wanted to hook up with you,
talk to you about what we were
talking about in your car.

56:25.442 --> 56:27.376
Okay.

56:27.444 --> 56:30.971
It makes you feel good,
putting what you know to use?

56:33.551 --> 56:36.452
- How'd you know that, Lowell?
- It's obvious, isn't it?

56:39.590 --> 56:41.922
Hello?
Are you there?

56:41.992 --> 56:44.460
Yeah.

56:44.528 --> 56:47.053
Look, um...

56:47.131 --> 56:49.395
Thanks for talking.
I'm sorry I woke you up.

56:49.466 --> 56:53.061
- I didn't know.
- It's okay.

57:01.579 --> 57:05.413
Lowell.

57:05.482 --> 57:07.416
Who is this?

57:07.484 --> 57:10.078
<i>Do not call here!</i>
<i>Do not...</i>

57:34.712 --> 57:36.646
What are you
gonna get us?

57:36.714 --> 57:38.705
Tempura.

57:42.586 --> 57:45.077
The Internet said you did
graduate work at Wisconsin,

57:45.155 --> 57:48.647
then went to U.C. La Jolla
with Professor Herbert?

57:48.726 --> 57:51.126
- Marcus...
- Marcuse. Yeah.

57:51.195 --> 57:53.493
He was my mentor.

