01:58:48.647 --> 01:58:51.673
Real selective. About as hard to get
ahold of as the Manhattan phone book.

01:58:51.750 --> 01:58:55.550
Well, it's authoritive...
and overwhelmingly documented.

01:58:55.621 --> 01:58:58.613
And it's bullshit. And if
I'm right, are you gonna put...

01:58:58.691 --> 01:59:01.888
the <i>Journal's</i> reputation behind a story
that's gonna blow up in your face?

01:59:01.961 --> 01:59:05.863
I'll take a look at what you got
but I'm not moving any deadlines
because you say so.

01:59:13.439 --> 01:59:15.373
Are you all right?

01:59:17.643 --> 01:59:19.577
Yeah.

01:59:28.887 --> 01:59:31.287
Officer Muravchick?

01:59:31.357 --> 01:59:34.383
Thank you.

01:59:34.460 --> 01:59:36.860
Officer Muravchick,
how are you?

01:59:36.929 --> 01:59:39.022
- I'm Sandra Sutherland.
- How do you do?

01:59:39.098 --> 01:59:41.157
Fine, thank you.
I'm doing a background check.

01:59:41.233 --> 01:59:43.167
Mind if I sit down?

01:59:45.371 --> 01:59:49.137
Your Honor,
could I have a word with you?

01:59:49.208 --> 01:59:52.974
You presided in a dispute
over support payments.

01:59:53.045 --> 01:59:56.344
Jeffrey Wigand?
Yeah, I cited him.

01:59:56.415 --> 02:00:00.476
CBS is under criticism because
the CBS News program, <i>60 Minutes,</i>

02:00:00.552 --> 02:00:02.520
will not be presenting
an interview...

02:00:02.588 --> 02:00:05.489
What the hell
are you doing?

02:00:05.557 --> 02:00:07.582
What does it look like
I'm doing? I'm editing.

02:00:07.660 --> 02:00:10.527
No, no, no that. I'm talking
about the Associated Press.

02:00:10.596 --> 02:00:15.192
They got the story that
we pulled this interview,
and they talked to Mike and I.

02:00:15.267 --> 02:00:17.258
Did you tell them
that we were lying?

02:00:17.336 --> 02:00:19.304
No!
I should have.

02:00:19.371 --> 02:00:21.566
I told them I disagreed
with you, Mike and Kluster...

02:00:21.640 --> 02:00:24.473
that this segment
is as good as the original.

02:00:24.543 --> 02:00:26.670
<i>I'm not lying for you.</i>
<i>I'm not gonna shut up for you.</i>

02:00:26.745 --> 02:00:29.612
<i>- Not on any of it.</i>
- Hey, I'm not gonna fire you.

02:00:29.682 --> 02:00:32.708
Okay? Take a vacation. Now!

02:00:36.388 --> 02:00:40.017
<i>Lowell? Look, I've decided</i>
<i>to preface Sunday's show.</i>

02:00:40.092 --> 02:00:42.890
I did three minutes on the
<i>Evening News.</i> You'll want to see it.

02:00:42.961 --> 02:00:45.987
- Where are you going?
- I've been banished...

02:00:46.065 --> 02:00:49.296
<i>in lieu of being fired.</i>

02:00:49.368 --> 02:00:52.337
<i>I took off on Tisch.</i>
<i>I took off on Corporate.</i>

02:00:52.404 --> 02:00:55.032
They'll know they're not, uh, going
to see everything on Sunday night.

02:00:56.341 --> 02:00:59.572
I don't know. How does that
get Wigand on the air?

02:00:59.645 --> 02:01:01.772
Do me a favor,
will you? Spare me.

02:01:01.847 --> 02:01:04.315
For God's sake, get in the
real world. What do you think?

02:01:04.383 --> 02:01:07.978
I'm going to resign in protest
to force it on the air?

02:01:08.053 --> 02:01:10.954
The answer's no. I don't plan
to spend the end of my days...

02:01:11.023 --> 02:01:14.049
wandering in the wilderness
of National Public Radio.

02:01:14.126 --> 02:01:16.060
That decision
I've already made.

02:01:18.063 --> 02:01:20.463
<i> This Sunday,</i>
<i>Wallace will broadcast a report...</i>

02:01:20.532 --> 02:01:24.798
<i>on the tobacco industry,</i>
<i>including the tough tactics</i>
<i>tobacco companies employ...</i>

02:01:24.870 --> 02:01:27.668
to keep a lid on information
that might be damaging.

02:01:27.740 --> 02:01:30.538
Is there information
that people should have...

02:01:30.609 --> 02:01:34.943
that they're not going to have
because you're not going to
broadcast this interview?

02:01:35.013 --> 02:01:39.074
- Yes.
- Today, CBS News president
Eric Kluster...

02:01:39.151 --> 02:01:41.915
<i>defended the network's decision</i>
<i>not to broadcast...</i>

02:01:41.987 --> 02:01:44.956
<i>key portions</i>
<i>of the controversial interview.</i>

02:01:45.023 --> 02:01:47.821
<i>Mr. Kluster said, quote,</i>
<i>"The atmosphere is tougher than ever."</i>

02:01:47.893 --> 02:01:50.384
- Where's the rest?
- Dan.

02:01:50.462 --> 02:01:52.396
Where the hell's the rest?

02:01:52.464 --> 02:01:55.433
<i>- Nebraska football</i>
<i>fans voiced their criticism...</i>
- You cut it!

02:01:55.501 --> 02:01:58.402
<i>Coming up in</i>
<i>Bernard Goldberg's America.</i>

02:01:58.470 --> 02:02:01.462
- You cut the guts out of what I said!
- It was a time consideration...

02:02:01.540 --> 02:02:04.373
Time? Bullshit!
You corporate lackey.

02:02:04.443 --> 02:02:08.277
Who told <i>you</i> your incompetent
little fingers have the
requisite skills to edit me?

02:02:08.347 --> 02:02:11.077
I'm trying to Band-Aid a situation
here, and you're too dim...

02:02:11.150 --> 02:02:13.516
Mike. Mike. Mike.

02:02:13.585 --> 02:02:17.612
"Mike"? Mike!

02:02:17.689 --> 02:02:19.486
Try "Mr. Wallace."

02:02:19.558 --> 02:02:23.426
We work in the same corporation. Doesn't
mean we work in the same profession.

02:02:23.495 --> 02:02:26.089
Now, now what are you going to do now?
You going to finesse me?

02:02:26.165 --> 02:02:30.499
Lawyer me some more? I've been
in this profession 50 fucking years!

02:02:30.569 --> 02:02:33.436
You and the people you work for
are destroying the most respected,

02:02:33.505 --> 02:02:36.474
the highest rated, the most
profitable show on this network.

02:02:52.524 --> 02:02:55.857
Here. These are
their leads, their sources.

02:02:55.928 --> 02:02:59.193
- I want you to have your reporters...
- Suein Hwang and Milo Geyelin.

02:02:59.264 --> 02:03:01.459
Have them make
their own calls.

02:03:01.533 --> 02:03:06.300
They'll find that these sources
have a different story than
the one that's in the dossier.

02:03:07.573 --> 02:03:09.507
Push the deadline,
Charlie.

02:03:14.746 --> 02:03:19.080
I'll push it for a week.
I want Milo and Suein to go through it.

02:03:33.332 --> 02:03:35.391
What do you want
to buy him for a gift?

02:03:35.467 --> 02:03:39.233
<i>Mmm, he's into</i>
<i>kind of little cars that, um...</i>

02:03:39.304 --> 02:03:41.534
- That remote control thing?
- Yeah.

02:03:41.607 --> 02:03:43.905
All right.
We'll go do that tomorrow.

02:03:43.976 --> 02:03:48.345
<i> The 63-36 vote was three</i>
<i>shy of the two-thirds needed to pass...</i>

02:03:48.413 --> 02:03:50.847
- Mom. There's Dad.
- Yes?

02:03:50.916 --> 02:03:54.317
<i>- On the TV.</i>
<i>- ... dating back to 1986.</i>

02:03:54.386 --> 02:03:56.547
The most recent trouble
for Wigand occurred here...

02:03:56.622 --> 02:03:58.749
And in local news,
WLKO, Louisville,

02:03:58.824 --> 02:04:01.418
has gained access
to a 500-page dossier...

02:04:01.493 --> 02:04:04.394
<i>on former Brown & Williamson</i>
<i>research head, Jeffrey Wigand,</i>

02:04:04.463 --> 02:04:08.331
<i>detailing charges of shoplifting</i>
<i>and failing to pay child support.</i>

02:04:08.400 --> 02:04:10.391
Wigand is currently teaching
chemistry and Japanese...

02:04:10.469 --> 02:04:12.403
<i>at the</i>
<i>DuPont Manual High School.</i>

02:04:12.471 --> 02:04:14.405
<i>Maria.</i>

02:04:36.060 --> 02:04:38.324
<i> Thousands of documents</i>
<i>from inside the tobacco industry...</i>

02:04:38.396 --> 02:04:40.489
<i>have surfaced</i>
<i>over the past year.</i>

02:04:40.564 --> 02:04:42.589
<i>Documents that</i>
<i>appear to confirm...</i>

02:04:42.667 --> 02:04:44.601
what a former
U.S. Surgeon general...

02:04:44.669 --> 02:04:48.537
and the current head of the Food and
Drug Administration have been saying.

02:04:48.606 --> 02:04:51.234
We learned of a tobacco insider
who could tell us...

02:04:51.309 --> 02:04:55.302
<i>whether or not the tobacco industry</i>
<i>has been leveling with the public.</i>

02:04:55.379 --> 02:04:57.313
<i>That insider was formerly...</i>

02:04:57.381 --> 02:05:00.316
<i>a highly-placed executive</i>
<i>with a tobacco company.</i>

02:05:00.384 --> 02:05:04.218
<i>But we cannot broadcast what critical</i>
<i>information about tobacco,</i>

02:05:04.288 --> 02:05:07.587
<i>addiction and public health</i>
<i>he might be able to offer.</i>

02:05:07.658 --> 02:05:11.492
<i>Why? Because he had to sign</i>
<i>a confidentiality agreement...</i>

02:05:11.562 --> 02:05:13.928
<i>with the tobacco company</i>
<i>he worked for.</i>

02:05:13.998 --> 02:05:17.126
<i>The management of CBS</i>
<i>has told us...</i>

02:05:17.201 --> 02:05:19.328
<i>that knowing</i>
<i>he had that agreement...</i>

02:05:19.403 --> 02:05:21.871
<i>if we were to broadcast</i>
<i>an interview with him,</i>

02:05:21.939 --> 02:05:25.898
<i>CBS could be faced with</i>
<i>a multi-billion dollar lawsuit.</i>

02:05:25.977 --> 02:05:29.606
<i>The fact is, we are not allowed</i>
<i>even to mention his name...</i>

02:05:29.680 --> 02:05:32.410
or the name of the company
he worked for.

02:05:32.483 --> 02:05:36.817
And, of course, we cannot
show you his face.

02:05:36.887 --> 02:05:39.981
And your confidentiality
agreement with...

02:05:40.057 --> 02:05:42.617
- Is still in force?
- Yes, it is.

02:05:42.693 --> 02:05:45.821
<i>So what are they gonna do?</i>
<i>Sue you for making this appearance?</i>

02:05:45.896 --> 02:05:48.262
<i>I would bet on it.</i>

02:05:48.332 --> 02:05:51.324
<i> The former executive</i>
<i>has reason to bet on being sued,</i>

02:05:51.402 --> 02:05:54.303
for major cigarette
manufacturers...

02:06:13.391 --> 02:06:16.360
Yeah.

02:06:16.427 --> 02:06:18.895
You disappeared on me.

02:06:18.963 --> 02:06:22.296
- How long you staying?
- I disappeared on you?

02:06:22.366 --> 02:06:25.028
All right.
What did you think?

02:06:26.103 --> 02:06:28.401
I think it was
a disgrace.

02:06:51.996 --> 02:06:55.727
- Still no answer.
- Get me the manager's office.

02:06:56.934 --> 02:06:59.198
David. David, you've got
a call on line four.

02:06:59.270 --> 02:07:02.330
I think you
better take it.

02:07:02.406 --> 02:07:04.397
This is David McDougal.
How can I help you?

02:07:04.475 --> 02:07:08.343
Mr. McDougal, my name is Lowell Bergman.
I'm a producer for <i>60 Minutes.</i>

02:07:08.412 --> 02:07:13.782
I'm concerned for a friend of mine
who's staying at your hotel right now.

02:07:20.424 --> 02:07:22.551
Mr. Wigand?

02:07:22.626 --> 02:07:24.560
Mr. Wigand?

02:07:30.201 --> 02:07:33.364
I-I think I need to call the police.
He won't respond.

02:07:33.437 --> 02:07:36.167
No, no, don't call the police. Just
tell him I'm on the phone with you.

02:07:36.240 --> 02:07:38.708
My name is Lowell Bergman.
Just tell him that.

02:07:38.776 --> 02:07:43.304
Mr. Wigand, Mr. Bergman
is on the telephone.

02:07:43.380 --> 02:07:45.871
Did he hear you?

02:07:45.950 --> 02:07:48.282
You're breaking up. I can't hear you.

02:07:48.352 --> 02:07:50.946
What about now?

02:07:51.021 --> 02:07:53.546
- What?
- Hello? Can you hear me now?

02:09:01.258 --> 02:09:05.160
- What's happening?
- He doesn't seem to be listening.

02:09:05.229 --> 02:09:09.131
All right. Now listen to me.
I want you... I want you to tell him...

02:09:09.200 --> 02:09:11.634
in these words:
Get on the fucking phone.

02:09:11.702 --> 02:09:13.966
I-I can't say that.

02:09:14.038 --> 02:09:16.563
No, you can. Tell him
to get on the fucking phone!

02:09:16.640 --> 02:09:19.734
He told me to tell you
to get on the... fucking phone!

02:09:25.749 --> 02:09:28.650
You manipulated me into this.

02:09:28.719 --> 02:09:30.983
- That's bullshit, Jeff.
- You greased the rails.

02:09:31.055 --> 02:09:35.185
I greased the rails for a guy who wanted
to say "yes." I helped him to say "yes."

02:09:35.259 --> 02:09:37.887
That's all.
You're not a robot, Jeff.

02:09:37.962 --> 02:09:40.897
- All right? You got a mind
of your own, don't you?
- " Up to you, Jeffrey.

02:09:40.965 --> 02:09:43.160
"That's the power you have,
Jeffrey.

02:09:43.234 --> 02:09:45.702
Vital inside information
the American public need to know."

02:09:45.769 --> 02:09:49.227
Lowell Bergman... the hotshot who never
met a source he couldn't turn around.

02:09:49.306 --> 02:09:51.501
I fought for you,
and I still fight for you!

02:09:51.575 --> 02:09:54.237
You fought for me?
You manipulated me...

02:09:54.311 --> 02:09:57.371
into where I am now... staring
at the Brown & Williamson building!

02:09:57.448 --> 02:10:00.645
It's all dark except the tenth floor.
That's the legal department.

02:10:00.718 --> 02:10:04.586
That's where they
fuck with my life.

02:10:07.691 --> 02:10:09.625
Jeffrey, where you going
with this?

02:10:11.262 --> 02:10:14.026
So, where you going?

02:10:18.202 --> 02:10:21.035
You are... important...

02:10:21.105 --> 02:10:24.006
to a lot of people,
Jeffrey.

02:10:24.074 --> 02:10:26.133
You think about that.

02:10:27.211 --> 02:10:29.145
You think about them.

02:10:42.226 --> 02:10:44.626
I'm running out
of heroes, man.

02:10:45.729 --> 02:10:47.856
Guys like you
are in short supply.

02:10:54.004 --> 02:10:55.938
Yeah, guys like you too.

02:11:00.711 --> 02:11:02.804
Where are you, anyway?

02:11:02.880 --> 02:11:07.408
I'm on a leave of absence.
Forced vacation.

02:11:09.586 --> 02:11:12.783
- You try and have a good time.
- Yeah.

02:11:12.856 --> 02:11:15.154
Yeah, I will.

02:11:29.307 --> 02:11:32.367
I'm Lowell Bergman. I'm from <i>60 Minutes.</i>
You know, you take the <i>60 Minutes...</i>

02:11:32.443 --> 02:11:34.968
out of that sentence,
nobody returns your phone calls.

02:11:36.247 --> 02:11:40.047
<i>Maybe Wigand's right.</i>
<i>Maybe I'm hooked.</i>

02:11:41.385 --> 02:11:43.319
What am I hooked on?

02:11:43.387 --> 02:11:45.651
The rush of <i>60 Minutes?</i>

02:11:45.723 --> 02:11:49.523
<i>What the hell for?</i>
<i>"Infotainment"!</i>

02:11:49.594 --> 02:11:51.858
It's so fucking useless,
all of it.

02:11:51.929 --> 02:11:55.660
So it's a big country with a free press.
You can go and work somewhere else.

02:11:55.733 --> 02:11:57.826
"Free press"?
The press is free.

02:11:57.902 --> 02:12:01.565
For anyone who owns one.
Larry Tisch has a free press.

02:12:01.639 --> 02:12:03.834
- Get some perspective, Lowell.
- I got perspective.

02:12:03.908 --> 02:12:05.899
No, you do not.

02:12:07.345 --> 02:12:09.836
From my perspective,

02:12:09.914 --> 02:12:13.816
what's been going on and what
I've been doing is ridiculous.

02:12:13.885 --> 02:12:16.217
- It's half-measures.
<i>- You're not listening.</i>

02:12:22.627 --> 02:12:25.619
Really know what you're
going to do before you do it.

02:13:07.271 --> 02:13:09.364
<i>I've got Richard Scruggs on the phone.</i>

02:13:09.440 --> 02:13:12.341
Patch him through.

02:13:12.410 --> 02:13:15.208
Well, Lowell, you are
not gonna believe this.

02:13:15.279 --> 02:13:19.579
The governor of Mississippi
is suing his own attorney general...

02:13:19.650 --> 02:13:23.245
to abandon litigation
against Big Tobacco.

02:13:23.321 --> 02:13:27.223
- Oh, good.
- But now that the version
without Jeff ran,

02:13:27.291 --> 02:13:30.624
what's the chance of getting
his interview on the air?

02:13:33.097 --> 02:13:35.190
- Hello?
- Yeah, I'm here.

02:13:35.266 --> 02:13:37.632
What chance is there of getting
Jeff's interview on the air?

02:13:37.702 --> 02:13:39.636
Less than great.

02:13:44.308 --> 02:13:46.606
I'd be lying to you
if I did not tell you...

02:13:46.677 --> 02:13:50.078
how important it was
in the court of public opinion.

02:13:50.147 --> 02:13:52.809
I'd be lying to you
if I didn't tell you...

02:13:52.883 --> 02:13:56.649
I'm about out of moves,
Dick.

02:13:58.889 --> 02:14:00.857
All right.
See ya.

02:14:23.014 --> 02:14:25.642
Hi.

02:14:27.385 --> 02:14:31.719
So, what are you folks
doing... here in Lincoln?

02:14:32.823 --> 02:14:36.816
- Geology survey.
- Geology?

02:14:36.894 --> 02:14:39.920
Yeah?
Really?

02:14:39.997 --> 02:14:41.931
How about you?

02:14:43.334 --> 02:14:45.894
I work for CBS News.

02:14:45.970 --> 02:14:48.461
Oh, yeah?

02:15:15.800 --> 02:15:18.360
Just ran into
two of your geologists.

02:15:18.436 --> 02:15:20.961
Geologists whose hands
aren't all chewed up.

02:15:21.038 --> 02:15:25.099
Lowell, do not...
screw this up.

02:15:25.176 --> 02:15:27.542
We are a week away
from an arrest.

02:15:27.611 --> 02:15:31.945
- So I'll hold it. And?
- We'll give you a heads-up
before we launch.

02:15:32.016 --> 02:15:34.507
- How long?
- Three hours.

02:15:34.585 --> 02:15:36.519
<i>You got a deal.</i>

02:15:51.836 --> 02:15:55.499
<i>... like the testimony before Congress</i>
<i>of Dr. Wigand's former boss,</i>

02:15:55.573 --> 02:15:59.339
<i>Brown & Williamson's chief</i>
<i>executive officer, Thomas Sandefur.</i>

02:15:59.410 --> 02:16:01.640
I believe that nicotine
is not addictive.

02:16:01.712 --> 02:16:04.203
I believe Mr. Sandefur
perjured himself...

02:16:04.281 --> 02:16:07.978
- because I watched those
testimonies very carefully.
- All of us did.

02:16:08.052 --> 02:16:10.247
There was this
whole line of people,

02:16:10.321 --> 02:16:12.846
whole line of C.E.O.'s
up there all swearing.

02:16:12.923 --> 02:16:16.017
Part of the reason I'm here
is that I felt...

02:16:16.093 --> 02:16:18.288
that their representation...

02:16:47.725 --> 02:16:49.659
...can be more rapidly absorbed
in the lung...

02:16:49.727 --> 02:16:51.853
and therefore affect the brain
and central nervous system.

02:17:16.554 --> 02:17:18.487
- Hello?
- Jim, it's Lowell.

02:17:18.556 --> 02:17:22.287
- Hey, where are you?
- Remember that night at P.J.'s?

02:17:22.359 --> 02:17:25.886
You asked me if we were
sitting on something explosive.
Well, we're not sitting on it.

02:17:25.963 --> 02:17:29.660
CBS Corporate leaned on CBS News,
which yanked an interview we did...

02:17:29.733 --> 02:17:33.691
with a top-ranking tobacco scientist,
corporate officer.

02:17:33.771 --> 02:17:35.830
They're trying to
close down the story.

02:17:35.906 --> 02:17:39.171
You mean, <i>60 Minutes</i>
is letting CBS Corporate...

02:17:39.243 --> 02:17:41.609
decide what is
or is not news?

02:17:41.679 --> 02:17:44.307
What's Wallace think
about this? Or Hewitt, or...

02:17:44.380 --> 02:17:46.508
How prominent?
What kind of placement?

02:17:46.584 --> 02:17:50.041
Oh, come on, Lowell. This is
<i>The New York Times.</i> I don't know.

02:17:50.120 --> 02:17:54.317
Well, until you do, all I can
tell you is what you already know.

02:17:54.391 --> 02:17:56.382
They will not
air an interview.

02:17:56.459 --> 02:17:58.860
Call me back in ten.

02:18:06.670 --> 02:18:08.968
